# DinoRand test/dev configuration — copy to `.env` (gitignored) and set your local install paths.
#
# The room round-trip integration tests prefer REAL game files when these point at your installs,
# and otherwise fall back to DMCA-safe synthetic mock rooms (so CI, which never has game files, still
# runs them). `.env` holds per-machine PATHS ONLY — never game bytes — and is never committed.
#
# An already-exported shell environment variable wins over the value here.

# DC1 (Dino Crisis 1) — a directory that contains a `Data/` folder of st*.dat rooms, OR a parent of one
# (e.g. the GOG install root, or a localized subfolder like `english/`).
DINORAND_DC1_DIR=/path/to/DinoCrisis1

# DC2 (Dino Crisis 2, Classic REbirth basis) — the install root that contains `rebirth/Data/ST*.DAT`,
# or point it straight at a directory of ST*.DAT rooms.
DINORAND_DC2_DIR=/path/to/DinoCrisis2
